Fuck. ⁣
⁣
This really hurts. ⁣
⁣
Still trying to process this news today. No doubt this post is a lame attempt at a bit of catharsis, but can you really blame me?⁣
⁣
Before Ken Block, fifteen52 was just a tiny, (barely even) niche wheel brand run by a trio of car nerds. We were having fun but still dreaming of finding a wider audience. And then came @brianscotto and his bff Ken Block. “You guys wanna make wheels for KB’s next Gymkhana video?”⁣
⁣
Through the steepest technical and marketing learning curves we ever experienced, KB stayed with us. When a big name and decades-old wheel company tried to throw huge $$$ at him to ditch us, KB stayed with us. When people within his own organization told him he should consider this other trendy wheel company, KB stayed with us. ⁣
⁣
Loyalty and friendship are rare when it comes to big business, but those who knew Ken best knew those values meant more to him than money. ⁣
⁣
Working with Ken Block offered my professional career opportunities that a younger me could have only dreamt of. For that I will always be grateful. ⁣
⁣
Over the next few weeks there are going to be hundreds of well-deserved tributes to a man know internationally as an amazing driver, industry icon, and marketing genius. With my small voice I just want to say that, more than any of that, he was also a truly good dude, friend, and family man. ⁣
From @eivindknutsen - too good not to share ❤️ #kb43 #kb43ver

Happy Re-Birthday to our girl, Akane!⁣
⁣
As some of you know, 4 years ago today Noriko donated her bone marrow to Akane in the hopes of finally curing her leukemia. ⁣
⁣
Four years later and all is well. Actually, it’s beyond well - Akane is doing great and we’re now one year away from her being considered basically cured! ⁣
⁣
She’s finishing up her sophomore year at UCLA and maintaining a perfect 4.0 GPA - and that’s in a STEM curriculum 😳⁣
⁣
Noriko and I couldn’t be more proud of her, and more than ever before her future looks so bright ❤️⁣
⁣
Four years ago today was the most challenging event our family has ever been through. Nothing at all was even close to certain and all we could hope for was just to keep our girl alive for as long as possible. ⁣
⁣
To see Akane today so healthy and thriving is truly a blessing and something we refuse to take for granted. We cherish every moment with her and with each passing re-birthday we grow more and more confident that truly the best is yet to come 🙏⁣
⁣
#fuckcancer #acutelymphoblasticleukemia #bonemarrowtransplant #survivor #akanestrong

Now that the 16” @rmlwheels Snowflakes are in production it’s time to move on to the next (and possibly last) version of the Snowflake design - the 18x8.5 and 19x8.5 sizes. 
⁣
I’ve updated the design a bit for these diameters to better suit the newer Mk7/Mk8 GTI/R models they’ll likely be used with. ⁣
⁣
After these I’m stoked to move on to some other non-VW designs. I believe the RML concept applies to all kinds of iconic OE wheel designs from the ‘80s and ‘90s and it’s going to be really interesting to see if I’m right 😉⁣
⁣
#rml #rmlwheels

Back in the day when fifteen52 was making the RML Snowflakes we had a run of mini, CNC-milled, billet-aluminum mini-flakes made. They cost us way more than you’d think, but people seemed to dig them. ⁣
⁣
Upon starting up RML again on my own, from the beginning I new I wanted to make another run of mini Snowflakes, but this time using the new updated 18”/19” design.
⁣
I hit up my buddy Justin from @zealous_mfg to see if he’d do it as a side project. Justin loves cool and silly shit like this and it really shows - check out the RML logo center cap engraving 😍⁣
⁣
He still needs to drill the bolt holes but I’ll soon have these in stock and up on the RML website 🍻⁣
⁣
#rml #rmlsnowflakes

I’m really stoked to be able to finally get this updated 18/19” version of the RML Snowflake wheel to market for the newer-chassis VWs. ⁣
⁣
Compared to the original 15” version, I updated the design a bit to better suit the aesthetics of the modern cars, while also addressing the need for better brake clearance and higher offsets. ⁣
⁣
I’ve made a lot of jokes and comments about it already, but I honestly do think this wheel design could easily have been a perfect match for VW’s 40th Anniversary Edition Mk8 GTI 🍻⁣
⁣
Check out the rmlwheels.com website: I’ve got 18” and 19” versions of this wheel available to order in either forged or flow-form spec. ⁣
⁣
#rml #rmlwheels

It’s #KBMemories day ☺️

After the 2013 SEMA show, @mattcrooke and I were asked to deliver the Focus ST we built for KB as part of the collab project we did with him and @fordperformance called @projectrst.⁣
⁣
We were to drive the car from Las Vegas to Ken’s home in Park City, Utah, and then fly back to LA. ⁣
⁣
The drive was beautiful and even though there was almost no snow yet in Park City, you could tell it was coming. Soon. And Ken was stoked to be there in one of his most favorite places in the world. ⁣
⁣
KB offered to put us up for the night in his guest room. ⁣
⁣
After getting some photo opps with the Focus and his dogs, Yuki and Bentley, we checked out his amazing Hoonigan Racing HQ facility. That evening Ken took us to dinner at one of his favorite local sushi joints. KB was a demon for Japanese food and he was known for being super picky about his choices for sake. Let’s just say that dinner that night did not disappoint. ⁣
⁣
It was our first time being able to just chill with Ken for more than 15 minutes and while Matt and I did our best not to fanboi the crap out of him, we did get a chance to discuss his perspective on a lot of different things. I’ll never forget how he explained that to him, driving sideways at 100+ through a dense forest of immovable trees seemed way less risky than driving F1. To KB, having a wide variety of different partial grip situations felt more comfortable and controlled than the on/off traction nature of the fastest tarmac racecars. Considering the brilliant car-control KB demonstrated time and again, his thinking definitely made sense. ⁣
⁣
No doubt to Ken it was just another day hanging out and talking car stuff to a couple fellow car nerds, but for me it was truly a special memory, because it not only confirmed what I already knew: Ken Block has always been just a genuine and extremely humble person; it also helped me feel that from that point on he wasn’t just a business associate, but he was also a friend. And anyone who has ever been so lucky to think of KB as a friend knows exactly how special that is. ⁣
⁣
#KBMemories #KB43VER #KenBlock
